      "message": "Issue: test_local_user and local_readonly_user are both created using ${test_user_password} (TestPwd123). Using the same password makes it harder to confirm that a test is failing because of a role restriction rather than a credential issue. A dedicated variable for the readonly user password (e.g. ${local_readonly_password}) would make each user\u0027s credentials independently traceable in logs.\n\nFix: Add a separate variable ${local_readonly_user_password} TestPwd123 (can share the same value initially but makes each credential independently overridable) and use it in Redfish Create User ${local_readonly_user} ${local_readonly_user_password} ... and Redfish.Login ${local_readonly_user} ${local_readonly_user_password}.\n\nWhy: Improves test clarity and makes credential-related failures easier to diagnose independently.",
